This paper is likely to belong to the database (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS) categories because it presents an algorithm for maintaining data structures efficiently. The leapfrog triejoin is a data structure used in database systems, and the paper proposes an incremental maintenance algorithm for it. Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories because the leapfrog triejoin is used in machine learning algorithms. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) category because the leapfrog triejoin is used in distributed systems.
